## useEditionList() function

> This API is provided as a preview for developers and may change based on feedback that we receive. Do not use this API in a production environment.
> 

Use this to get a list of NFT tokens of your ERC721 contract.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
declare function useEditionList(contract: Erc1155<any> | undefined, queryParams?: QueryAllParams): react_query.UseQueryResult<{
    metadata: {
        [x: string]: _thirdweb_dev_sdk.Json;
        description?: string | undefined;
        image?: string | undefined;
        external_url?: string | undefined;
        animation_url?: string | undefined;
        name: string;
        id: BigNumber;
        uri: string;
    };
    supply: BigNumber;
}[] | undefined, unknown>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  contract | Erc1155&lt;any&gt; \| undefined | an instace of a contract that extends the Erc721 spec (nft collection, nft drop, custom contract that follows the Erc721 spec) |
|  queryParams | QueryAllParams | <i>(Optional)</i> query params to pass to the query for the sake of pagination |

<b>Returns:</b>

react\_query.UseQueryResult&lt;{ metadata: { \[x: string\]: \_thirdweb\_dev\_sdk.Json; description?: string \| undefined; image?: string \| undefined; external\_url?: string \| undefined; animation\_url?: string \| undefined; name: string; id: BigNumber; uri: string; }; supply: BigNumber; }\[\] \| undefined, unknown&gt;

a response object that includes an array of NFTs

## Example


```javascript
const { data: nfts, isLoading, error } = useNFTList(<YourERC721ContractInstance>, { start: 0, count: 100 });
```
